headlines.description: — Jayson Tatum scored 27 points, Jaylen Brown had 22 and the Boston Celtics beat the Cleveland Cavaliers 116-107 on Thursday night to improve to 12-0 at home.
headlines.shortLinkText: Celtics improve to 12-0 at home behind Jayson Tatum's 27 points in 116-107 win over Cavs

headlines.description: — The Chicago Bulls started the night by doing something their franchise hadn't seen since the Michael Jordan era.
headlines.shortLinkText: Bulls run out to huge lead, then hang on to beat Heat 124-116

headlines.description: — Naz Reid score 19 of his season-high 27 points in the first half, Karl-Anthony Towns had 21 points and a season-high 17 rebounds, and the Minnesota Timberwolves shook off an early 15-point deficit to beat Luka Doncic and the Dallas Mavericks 119-101...
headlines.shortLinkText: Naz Reid, Timberwolves shake off slow start, beat Luka Doncic and Mavs 119-101

headlines.description: — Nikola Jokic became the first NBA player with at least 10 triple-doubles in seven straight seasons as the Denver Nuggets beat the Brooklyn Nets 124-101 on Thursday night for their third consecutive win.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jokic gets his 10th triple-double of the season as the Nuggets beat the Nets 124-101

events.name: Utah Jazz at Portland Trail Blazers

headlines.description: — Collin Sexton scored 27 points, Simone Fonteccio had 24 and the Utah Jazz beat the struggling Portland Trail Blazers 122-114 on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Sexton and Fonteccio lead short-handed Jazz to 122-114 win over Trail Blazers

events.name: Oklahoma City Thunder at Sacramento Kings

headlines.description: — De’Aaron Fox scored 41 points and the Sacramento Kings beat Shai Gilgeous-Alexander and the Oklahoma City Thunder 128-123 on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: De’Aaron Fox scores 41 points as Kings beat Thunder 128-123

events.name: Golden State Warriors at LA Clippers

headlines.description: — James Harden scored his 25,000th career point while racking up a season-high 28 points, 15 assists and seven rebounds, and Kawhi Leonard added 27 points and eight rebounds in the Los Angeles Clippers' sixth straight victory, 121-113 over the...
headlines.shortLinkText: James Harden scores his 25,000th point, leads streaking Clippers past slumping Warriors 121-113
